intergovernmental fiscal relations in china siepr siepr stanford institute for economic policy research search the site enter your keywords main links home about siepr research at siepr education at siepr events at siepr people at siepr publications at siepr economics in the news support siepr contact us stay connected stay connected banner home publications profile display intergovernmental fiscal relations in china type scid working paper 305 author s annalisa fedelino teresa ter minassian published 12 1 06 region china download pdf abstract the authors provide an overview of the current system of intergovernmental fiscal relations in china highlighting the current imbalance between revenue sources and expenditure mandates which adversely affects all local governments especially the poorest they discuss other weaknesses of the system including the lack of significant own revenue sources for local governments their inadequate budget formulation and implementation procedures and the emergence of indirect forms of indebtedness and fiscal risks the authors go on to present policy options that address such weaknesses as redefining spending responsibilities creating enhanced own revenue sources for local governments redesigning transfer systems improving public financial management and enforcing prudent borrowing limits stanford university economics department stanford center for international development public policy program site map economic summit
